Package plugins

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Abs
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the absolute value of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Add
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the addition of the corresponding grid cells in two input rasters or one input raster and a constant value.
    AND
    This tool is a Boolean operator for which grid cells for which both input rasters have True values are assigned 1 in the output raster, otherwise grid cells are assigned a value of 0.
    ArcCos
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the inverse cosine of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    ArcSin
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the inverse sine of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    ArcTan
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the inverse tangent of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Ceil
    This tool returns the smallest (closest to negative infinity) value that is greater than or equal to the values in a raster.
    Cos
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the cosine of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Cosh
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the hyperbolic cosine of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Divide
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the division of the corresponding grid cells in two input rasters or one input raster and a constant value.
    EqualTo
    This tool assigns grid cells for which both input rasters (or one raster and a constant value) have equal values a new value of 1 (True) in the output raster.
    Exp
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is calculated as e to the power of the value of the corresponding grid cell in the input raster.
    Floor
    This tool returns the largest (closest to positive infinity) value that is less than or equal to the values in a raster.
    GreaterThan
    This tool assigns grid cells for which the first input raster (or constant value) is greater than the second input raster (or constant) a new value of 1 (True) in the output raster.
    GreaterThanEqualTo
    This tool assigns grid cells for which the first input raster (or constant value) is greater than or equal to the second input raster (or constant) a new value of 1 (True) in the output raster.
    IntDiv
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the integer division of the corresponding grid cells in two input rasters or one input raster and a constant value.
    IsNoData
    This tool can be used to identify areas of NoData values within an image.
    LessThan
    This tool assigns grid cells for which the first input raster (or constant value) is less than the second input raster (or constant) a new value of 1 (True) in the output raster.
    LessThanEqualTo
    This tool assigns grid cells for which the first input raster (or constant value) is less than or equal to the second input raster (or constant) a new value of 1 (True) in the output raster.
    Ln
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is calculated as the base e (constant approximately equal to 2.718282) logarithm of the value of the corresponding grid cell in the input raster.
    Log10
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is calculated as the base 10 logarithm of the value of the corresponding grid cell in the input raster.
    Log2
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is calculated as the base 2 logarithm of the value of the corresponding grid cell in the input raster.
    Max
    This tool returns a Max operation on two rasters or a raster and a constant value.
    Min
    This tool returns a Min operation on two rasters or a raster and a constant value.
    Modulo
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the remainder of division of the corresponding grid cells in two input rasters or one input raster and a constant value.
    Multiply
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the product of the corresponding grid cells in two input rasters or one input raster and a constant value i.e., multiplication.
    Negate
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to negative one times the corresponding grid cell in the input raster.
    NOT
    This tool is a Boolean operator for which grid cells for which the first input raster has a True value but not the second raster raster are assigned 1 in the output raster, otherwise grid cells are assigned a value of 0.
    NotEqualTo
    This tool assigns grid cells for which both input rasters (or one raster and a constant value) have unequal values a new value of 1 (True) in the output raster.
    OR
    This tool is a Boolean operator for which grid cells for which either input raster has a True value are assigned 1 in the output raster, otherwise grid cells are assigned a value of 0.
    Power
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is calculated value of one input raster raised to the power of a second input raster, a constant raised to the power of values in a raster, or a raster raised to the power of a constant.
    Reciprocal
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to one divided by the grid cell values in the input raster image.
    Round
    This tool rounds the values in an input image.
    Sin
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the sine of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Sinh
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the hyperbolic sine of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    SqrRt
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the square root of the value of the corresponding grid cell in the input raster.
    Square
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the square of the value of the corresponding grid cell in the input raster
    Subtract
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the subtraction of the corresponding grid cells in two input rasters or one input raster and a constant value.
    Tan
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the tangent of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Tanh
    This tool creates a new raster in which each grid cell is equal to the hyperbolic tangent of the corresponding grid cell in an input raster.
    Truncate
    This tool truncates the values in an input image to the desired number of decimal places.
    XOR
    This tool is a Boolean operator for which grid cells for which the first input raster has a True value but not the second raster are assigned 1 in the output raster, otherwise grid cells are assigned a value of 0.
